Sorry

It's a mistake. Please close the issue.

{{"None"}} and {{None}} are treated as the same value, but {{"First"}} and {{First}} are not. This inconsistency led to me wasting time wondering why the query didn't work, and then going to the docs and finding that they were wrong too.

The JQL parser should treat {{"None"}} as a text value, and {{None}} as a keyword, just as it does for {{"First"}} and {{First}}.

The [docs|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA040/Advanced+Searching#AdvancedSearching-cascadeOption%28%29] say that the correct JQL for searching for {{"None"}} is:

{quote}
referrer in cascadeOption("\"none"\","\"none"\")
{quote}

…but that's wrong too. Instead it should be:

{quote}
referrer in cascadeOption("\"none\"","\"none\"")
{quote}

**Steps to reproduce:**

# Create a Cascading Select custom field called "Test field"
# Add the following options to it:
#* First
#* First
#** None
# Create an issue named "No child" and set its *Test Field* value to *First*
# Create an issue named "Has child" and set its *Test Field* value to *First > None*
# Create an issue named "No parent" and leave its *Test Field* value undefined.
# Run the advanced search: {{"Test field" in cascadeOption(none)}}
The issue "No parent" should be found.
# Run the advanced search: {{"Test field" in cascadeOption(First)}}
A JQL error should occur (more details below).
# Run the advanced search: {{"Test field" in cascadeOption("First")}}
The two issues "No child" and "Has child" should be found.
# Run the advanced search: {{"Test field" in cascadeOption("First", none)}}
Only the "No child" issue should be found.
# Run the advanced search: {{"Test field" in cascadeOption("First", "None")}}
Only the "Has child" issue should be found.

The JQL error message says 

{quote}
Incorrect number of arguments specified for the function 'cascadeOption'. Usages: cascadeOption(parentOption), cascadeOption(parentOption, childOption), cascadeOption(parentOption, "None")
{quote}

… but according to the [docs|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA040/Advanced+Searching#AdvancedSearching-cascadeOption%28%29] the value is {{none}} rather than {{"None"}}. This means that the error message should also be updated. Additionally, if the message is going to include the {{cascadeOption(parentOption, none)}} case, it should also include the {{cascadeOption(none)}} case. Alternatively just leave it as {{parentOption}} and {{childOption}}.

