When a new JIRA issue is created, JIRA currently only displays a popup window saying "a new JIRA issue has been created." But I do not think this is enough. For example, when users create a new JIRA issue on the issue navigator, they will have to refresh the Web browser by themselves to get the new JIRA issue listed on the research result.

It would be useful if JIRA provides an option that refreshes the current screen which a user is currently viewing after a new JIRA issue is created.

h3. Steps to Reproduce:
# Create a Custom Event in JIRA;
# Edit the workflow and change the Create Issue transition to use the Custom Event instead of the Issue Created event;
# Change your User Profile settings to enable the Autowatch feature;
# Create a new issue (using this workflow).

h3. Expected Results:
You'd be automatically added as a watcher to the issue after creating it.

h3. Actual Results:
The user is not added as a watcher to the issue.

